snippet.textDisplay:
This guy has the WORST VOICE I'VE EVER HEARD IN MY LIFE! Am I the only one who doesn't like listening to this guy's music? Because I am fed up of listening to this guy on the radio. His songs are so depressing they don't make any sense. Here's what I think of the songs that I've been hearing on the radio:

Someone You Loved: The beat and rhythm of this song is good, but this guy's cringey voice ruins the whole song.

Hold Me While You Wait: The worst song I've ever heard from him. It's depressing and miserable to listen to, but the end of the song is the worst part, because he literally shouts out "WON'T YOU STAY WIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIII..........." and I feel like I'm getting an earrape whenever I hear that part.

Bruises: It's depressing, it's miserable, it has no rhythm whatsoever, all I hear is the depressing sound of the piano and the terrible sound of his voice, especially during the chorus.

Before You Go: Don't like that song either especially the way when he says "BEFORE YOU GO" during the chorus.

I can think of 1000 songs that are much better than this guy's songs. For example, here's one worth listening to:
https://youtu.be/p3l7fgvrEKM

You’ll see that you’re not alone, that you shouldn’t be scared and that it’s okay to make mistakes. Just hang on a little longer, just stay strong a little more and before you know it you’ll see the light at the end of the tunnel. You’ll see your worth and how amazing you are as a person. You’ll  see that other people love you and need you in their lives. Look at yourself in the mirror and smile at yourself everyday because each smile will get you closer to loving yourself and becoming the best version of yourself. Don’t think you’re alone; you’re there, I’m here, we’re all here for you ☺️ So stay strong and keep fighting because it’s never a losing battle when you know yourself best.
